## Summary
This migration guide documents the upgrade from Flutter SDK 3.0 to 4.0, covering breaking changes including removal of `instance()` calls, Configuration object initialization, API method renames (`logEvent()` to `track()`, `uploadEvents()` to `flush()`), iOS platform requirement bump to 13.0, and Browser SDK 2 snippet replacement for Flutter Web.

